      <p>My then-agent took me to the Cafe to celebrate selling my novel. All I remember was that I wound up with spaghetti with meatballs by default, and was a little sad, because I don&#39;t really like them. Except for those meatballs. I don&#39;t know what they did to them, but they were so delicious! And the pasta was perfect, and there was a salad and something sweet afterwards, but mostly, revelatory meatballs. <br />I got on Alice&#39;s case several years ago when she was taken in by a charlatan out here who was building a development he called a &#8220;reserve&#8221; (thankfully the crash of 2008 saved us all), but if anyone deserves this, it&#39;s her. So exciting you got to interview her! </p>
