      <p>What an incredibly exciting interview to have done!<br />My husband and I made a pilgrimage to the Cafe from Australia by way of San Francisco (and in that same trip, incidentally, to the famed Zuni Cafe in SF, which was another total revelation). Though I know we ate amazingly well at Chez Panisse, I&#39;m a bit ashamed to admit I actually don&#39;t remember the specific dishes we had, which I still find odd given my clear memories of so many other meals in great restaurants! <br />Anyway, Molly, your description of how you felt when you left the place that first time really resonates, and it occurs to me maybe it doesn&#39;t matter that the exact meal from our visit is forgotten &#8211; what remains, six years after the fact, is the feeling we&#39;d experienced an &#39;event&#39;, not just in the food but in the care and sheer love shown for every aspect of our meal by the staff. It&#39;s such a rare and happy thing and we have high hopes of returning one of these days.</p>
