      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/09/september-6-2/#comment-43821"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-09-07T17:50:10-04:00">Monday, September 7, 2015 at 5:50 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have so loved her approach to honoring fresh produce. Most people think of her and veggies. But I also love her for something else. Many years ago, Alice offered a cookie recipe to a national women&#39;s magazine (I&#39;m thinking Better Homes and Gardens,but may be wrong.) I copied it into my spiral bound personal favorites cookbook, with attribution. The recipe was for a cinnamon almond wafer cookie, ingredients combined both on and then off the stove, and then shaped and chilled before slicing to bake. It remains the best cookie ever. My son grew up with them and no Christmas or birthday would be complete without them. Her cookie is our tradition. </p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-43822" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
