    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;d like to add my voice to yours and those who have commented here to remember the same sort of feelings after eating the food of Alice Waters at both the restaurant and the cafe.  I, too, prefer the cafe.  I also especially like her cookbook, The Art of Simple Food, and serving food from her recipes opens the same doors of joyous rightness with the world.  It reminds me of a book I read years ago by an Episcopalian priest, The Supper of the Lamb, which described the food we prepare as a kind of sacrament.</p>
<p>Your site is well worth my time and so was your book.  Thanks right back.</p>
